products.title: Bushranger Jarrah Bee Pollen Western Australian 200g
products.body_html:
This Jarrah Bee Pollen is harvested from pristine Jarrah Native Western Australian Forests, drawing nutrients from the ancient and rich Australian bush.

Jarrah Bee Pollen is only available seasonally due to its availability. 

Bee Pollen contains over 250 types of nutrients including vitamins, flavonoids, minerals, carbohydrates, lipids, amino acids & proteins

Serving Suggestions

Sprinkle ½ - 1 teaspoon on cereal or yoghurt, add to smoothies, or effective,  directly under the tongue.

Bee Pollen is best stored in the refrigerator to maintain it's crunch. 

Not recommended to be added to hot food or drinks.

products.body_html:

products.title: Bushranger Raw Creamed Honey Ginger
products.body_html:
This air-whipped cold set raw honey has a creamy texture and is an excellent healthy alternative for spreads on toast, crumpets, and bagels. It is exceptional used as icing on a cooled home baked cake.

Store this as you would store butter. Keep in the fridge to preserve consistency and take out of the fridge to soften up for spreading. Store at room temperature in winter. On hot days and during summer, store in the fridge.

This only contains Honey and Air. No dairy or any other additives.

PLEASE NOTE - Only available in the cooler months (April-October)

products.title: Australian Bio-dynamic Olive Oil 250ml
products.body_html:
Θείος Νίκος came to Australia from Kyparissia, a prestigious Olive growing
region in Greece in the 1960’s and planted his Olive groves in what has
now become one of Australia ’s premium food producing regions.

Today he tends to approximately 1500 Olive trees. He has always used his
traditional Greek farming practices that have been passed-on for many
generations and still today he follows the ancient ways ensuring the finest
tasting and purest olive oil.

This fine fruity Olive oil is a brilliant healthy addition to your favorite
salads, drizzled on your fish, meats or vegetables, added to pasta or simply as
a dipping for your favorite bread.

This is a true example of farm to plate produce. Only small batches are made
and it is only sold directly from the family.

products.title: Waradaa 33+ Rare Australian Manuka Honey MGO 1800 180g
products.body_html:
At 1800 of MGO per KG, our 33+ rated honey is the rarest Manuka honey at WARADAA harvested once in 5 years!

This supremely rich honey is very strong and powerful.

Waradaa is one of the foundational brands for the Australian Manuka Association, supported by the Australian Government and industry bodies. Honey that carries the AMHA’s Mark of Authenticity must be pure, natural Manuka honey, produced entirely in Australia, and tested by an independent, approved laboratory. Our production facilities also meet the highest honey health standards including AMHA authorization, HACCP, and BQUAL.

Our business is at the foremost a beekeeping business. We take great care with our bees and ensure our honey is made to the highest quality standards, preserving the natural taste, texture, and enzymes as nature intended. We differentiate ourselves based on:

  • Cold processing minimizing HMF (burnt/bitter taste)
  • Testing our product to ensure it is free of chemicals and meets strict quality standards
  • Applying rigid quality control to ensure consistency. All Honey Store products are certified by independent laboratories, ensuring strict quality control
  • Soft setting our honey to create a delicious, firm and shelf-stable product with a 5-year shelf life

products.body_html:
